Naval Fate

  Command line example adapted from Docopt's Naval Fate
  Source bu`http://docopt.org/`

Usage:
  run new SHIPS...
  run move SHIP X Y [--speed KN]
  run mine (set | remove) X Y  [--moored | --drifting]
  run (--help | -h)
  run --version

Commands:
  nb`new`
    Deploy one or more ships

  nb`move`
    Move the given ship

  nb`mine`
    Set or remove a mine

Parameters:
  SHIPS
    One or more ship names

  SHIP
    Ship name

Options:
  --speed, -s KN
    Speed in knots [default: 20]

  --moored
    Moored (anchored) mine

  --drifting
    Drifting mine

  --help, -h
    Show this message

  --version
    Show version number